                    "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4296138/use-wildcard-with-os-path-isfile/4296146#4296146",
                    "body": "<p><strong>Wildcards are expanded by shell</strong> and hence you can not use it with os.path.isfile()</p>\n\n<p>If you want to use wildcards, you could use <code>popen with shell = True</code> or <code>os.system()</code> </p>\n\n<pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; import os\n&gt;&gt;&gt; os.system('ls')\naliases.sh          \ndefault_bashprofile     networkhelpers          projecthelper.old           pythonhelpers           virtualenvwrapper_bashrc\n0\n&gt;&gt;&gt; os.system('ls *.old')\nprojecthelper.old\n0\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You could get the same effect with glob module too.</p>\n\n<pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; import glob\n&gt;&gt;&gt; glob.glob('*.old')\n['projecthelper.old']\n&gt;&gt;&gt; \n</code></pre>\n"
