                    "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4296138/use-wildcard-with-os-path-isfile/4296148#4296148",
                    "body": "<p><a href=\"http://docs.python.org/library/glob.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">glob</a> is what you need.</p>\n\n<pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; import glob\n&gt;&gt;&gt; glob.glob('*.rar')   # all rar files within the directory, in this case the current working one\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><code>os.path.isfile()</code> returns <code>True</code> if a path is an existing regular file. So that is used for checking whether a file already exists and doesn't support wildcards. <code>glob</code> does.</p>\n"
